                                        <assignee username="isaac">Isaac Huang</assignee>
                                    <reporter username="isaac">Isaac Huang</reporter>
                        <labels>
                            <label>zfs</label>
                    </labels>
                <created>Thu, 16 Oct 2014 03:43:01 +0000</created>
                <updated>Sat, 18 Oct 2014 02:51:34 +0000</updated>
                                                                                <due></due>
                            <votes>0</votes>
                                    <watches>2</watches>
                                                                            <comments>
                            <comment id="96654" author="isaac" created="Sat, 18 Oct 2014 02:51:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It seemed that with the code above, if user sets lu_cache_nr=LU_CACHE_NR_UNLIMITED (e.g. to work around &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-5747&quot; title=&quot;NULL pointer dereference in task_rq_lock when running mds-survey&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-5747&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-5747&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;), it&apos;d still get overwritten as LU_CACHE_NR_ZFS_LIMIT.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="96611" author="adilger" created="Fri, 17 Oct 2014 18:01:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Looks like this would be enough:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;        &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (strcmp(top-&amp;gt;ld_type-&amp;gt;ldt_name, LUSTRE_OSD_ZFS_NAME) == 0) {
                lu_cache_percent = 1;
                &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (lu_cache_nr == LU_CACHE_NR_UNLIMITED)
                        lu_cache_nr = LU_CACHE_NR_ZFS_LIMIT;
                &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; LU_SITE_BITS_MIN;
        }
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
